Sambhavna Seth‚Äôs full name is Sambhavna Surender Kumar Seth. We must have seen her on YouTube, in Big Boss, and in many bhojpuri songs. She had a lot of love for dance since childhood. From the very beginning, she wanted to become a heroine. To make a career, she went to Mumbai with her father and gave many auditions, but did not get work and came back to Delhi. She did not do any work for 1 year, then after gaining some confidence, she again came to Mumbai. Got a film after a lot of struggle. She has worked in songs of many big films but those songs did not become hits but everyone was quite impressed with her dance.
Then he got a chance to work in Bhojpuri songs. The first song became so famous that now she started getting a lot of work in the Bhojpuri industry. Time passed and she also appeared in many reality shows like Big Boss, Khatron ke khiladi and Desi Girl. Today she runs a YouTube channel named Sambhavna Seth Entertainment on which she posts vlogs.

snippet.title: S8E6 | Virender Sehwag | Breakfast with Champions ft Gaurav Kapur | @skodaindia     ‚Äã
snippet.description:
The season finale of ≈†KODA presents Breakfast with Champions ft. Gaurav Kapur has some royal swag! üèèüåü Say hello to The Nawab of Najafgarh, The Sultan of Multan. üëë

Virender Sehwag is a born entertainer and he continues to enthrall us with his take on his teammates and stories that are now cricketing folklore. From scooter rides with Ashish Nehra to pranking Sourav Ganguly, and from farm fresh buffalo milk to fine dining that Sachin introduced him to, this episode is a rollercoaster of laughter and nostalgia. 

Hear all about his banter with Shoaib Akhtar and the love he got from Pakistani shopkeepers, the invaluable advice Tiger Pataudi's gave him, how he had to return from the airport before his debut and the epic moment he scored 300 runs with a sensational six! 

This episode tastes best with garma-garam desi ghee ke Chole Bhature with Lassi in a kulhad.

Heyy Deyyss ‚ù§Ô∏è

Uncovering the Secrets of Karen Long Neck Village |‡Æµ‡Æø‡Æö‡Æø‡Æ§‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø‡Æ∞ ‡Æï‡Æø‡Æ∞‡Ææ‡ÆÆ ‡ÆÆ‡Æï‡Øç‡Æï‡Æ≥‡Øç üò± ‡Æá‡Æµ‡Øç‡Æ≥‡Øã ‡Æ™‡ØÜ‡Æ∞‡Æø‡ÆØ ‡Æï‡Æ¥‡ØÅ‡Æ§‡Øç‡Æ§‡Ææ ü§Ø ‚Äã 

We had an extraordinary encounter that left us in awe. We had the chance to witness an incredible experimental creation in the world of entertainment: a combination of a lion and a tiger known as the LIGAR. This magnificent breed is eight times larger than a typical lion or tiger, but despite its immense size, it had a surprising nature, almost like a giant toy.

here are some additional facts about ligers:
- Ligers are the largest known cat species in the world, even larger than their parents, the lion, and the tiger.
- Ligers have a unique appearance, with stripes from the tiger and a mane from the lion.
- Ligers are usually sterile and cannot reproduce, although there have been a few rare cases of ligers being able to mate with other ligers or with lions or tigers.
- Ligers are not found in the wild, as lions and tigers do not share the same habitats in the wild.
- Ligers are often bred in captivity, and there is some controversy surrounding the practice of breeding ligers and other hybrid animals.
- Ligers are known for their playful personalities and are often used in animal shows and attractions.
- Ligers have a lifespan of around 10-15 years, which is shorter than the lifespan of lions and tigers in the

But our adventure didn't stop there! We ventured into a village with a fascinating tradition that caught our attention. In Karen Gong Neck Village, we encountered a community of people known for their unique practice of elongating their necks. These polite and welcoming individuals sustain their livelihood by crafting and selling handmade items. To achieve elongated necks, they gradually add neck rings every four years, resulting in a truly remarkable sight.

here are some interesting facts about Karen Gong Neck Village:

- The Karen Long Neck tribe is originally from Myanmar (Burma) and migrated to Thailand in the 1980s.
- The women of the tribe wear brass rings around their necks, starting at a young age, which give the appearance of elongated necks. Contrary to popular belief, the rings do not actually lengthen the neck but rather push down the collarbone and ribcage to create the illusion of a longer neck.
- The Karen Long Neck tribe is just one of several hill tribes in northern Thailand, each with their own unique culture and traditions.
- The village is located in a mountainous region, surrounded by lush forests and rice paddies.
- Visitors to the village can learn about the tribe's traditional handicrafts, including weaving and embroidery, and purchase handmade souvenirs.
- The village is also home to a school, where children from the tribe can receive an education.
- The Karen Long Neck tribe has faced some controversy and criticism over the years, with some people arguing that the practice of wearing the neck rings is exploitative and objectifying. However, others argue that it is an important part of the tribe's cultural heritage and should be preserved.
- Despite the controversy, Karen Gong Neck Village remains a popular tourist destination, attracting visitors from all over the world who are interested in learning about the tribe's unique culture and traditions.

This captivating journey was filled with astonishing sights and remarkable cultural experiences.

Episode 3788: Pyarelal's Dilemma
--------------------------------------------------------
Pyaarelal gets into trouble as Sapna and Kalpana have accepted his proposal to get married. Earlier Sapna had not revealed her decision while Babita and Madhavi had asked Pyaarelal to accept Kalpana. As everyone discusses the matter at Popatlal's house, Dr. Hathi comes excited to his house. he announces that they have brought him another proposal for marriage. Anjali and Taarak discuss who will tell the truth to Sapna's family, he calls Sapna's mother but she thinks it to be a prank. Keep an eye out! 

Show Name ‚Äì Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast ‚Äì  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni
Episodes No - 3788, 3 June 2023
Produced By - Asit Kumar Modi

About the show: 
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired by the famous humorous column, Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer, Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada family which consists of businessman, Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal's wife, Daya & their naughty son, Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society, and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone.

Your favourite rappers from Hustle 2.0 reunite to bring to you The Hustle Reunion song which is a celebration of their journey on season 2 of Hustle.

snippet.description:
Thanks for watching Har Pal Geo. Please click here https://bit.ly/3rCBCYN to Subscribe and hit the bell icon to enjoy Top Pakistani Dramas and satisfy all your entertainment needs. Do you know Har Pal Geo is now available in the US? Share the News. Spread the word.

Tere Bin Episode 51 Teaser - 1st June 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

Writer: Nooran Makhdoom
Director: Siraj ul Haq
Producers: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi
Production House: 7th Sky Entertainment

Cast :
Yumna Zaidi as Meerab

Bushra Ansari as Salma

Fazila Qazi as Aneela
Farhan Ally Agha as Waqas
Seemi Pasha as Sabra

Haris Waheed

Suraj Tiwari has secured 917th rank in the Civil Services Examination 2022. In this video he is sharing his journey of preparation. This video will definitely motivate you.

Team Drishti wishes Suraj a very successful and fruitful career.

snippet.description:

Tere Bin Episode 50 - [Eng Sub] - Yumna Zaidi - Wahaj Ali - Digitally Presented by Jhalak Beauty Cream - 1st June 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Tere Bin Digitally Presented by Jhalak Beauty Cream

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

Writer: Nooran Makhdoom
Director: Siraj ul Haq
Producers: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad Qureshi

About The Show:
----------------------------
Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a comedy show inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around the Gada Family which consists of uneducated businessmen Jethalal Champaklal Gada, Jethalal‚Äôs Wife Daya & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society' and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of a problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. The housing society residents help each other find solutions when facing common, real-life challenges and getting involved in sticky situations.

snippet.description:
Click here to subscribe to SAB: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Episode 3787: Hum Dono Ki Haan Hai
--------------------------------------------------------
Pyaarelal decides to pick Kalpana after meeting with her parents, while Sapna's parents are waiting for his response. Babita and Madhavi advise Pyaarelal to accept Kalpana's proposal because they are unsure of Sapna's final decision. So Pyaarelal ultimately decides on Kalpana. When the marriage is restored, everyone rejoices. Sapna, on the other hand, agrees with the proposal. What would Pyaarelal's decision be now that both families have approved for him to be their son-in-law? Keep an eye out!

Tere Bin Episode 49 - [Eng Sub] - Yumna Zaidi - Wahaj Ali - Digitally Presented by Nisa BB Cream - 31st May 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Tere Bin Digitally presented by Nisa BB Cream

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

snippet.title: Meet India's Most RESPECTED Politician - Nitin Gadkari On Figuring Out 93 | Raj Shamani
snippet.description:
Co-presented to you by @MyGovIndia 

Order my first book 'Build, Don't Talk' here: https://amzn.eu/d/eCfijRu

Subscribe To Our Other YouTube Channels:-

https://www.youtube.com/@rajshamaniclips

https://www.youtube.com/@RajShamani.Shorts

--------------

Join us for an insightful conversation with Nitin Gadkari, an esteemed Indian politician and the current Minister of Road Transport and Highways of India, on our latest podcast episode! üåü

In this engaging discussion, we delve into Mr. Gadkari's visionary approach to infrastructure development, sustainable transportation, and his unwavering commitment to transforming India's road network. As one of the key architects behind numerous ambitious projects, he shares valuable insights on building world-class highways, promoting electric mobility, and implementing innovative solutions to tackle the challenges of urban congestion and pollution.

Get ready to gain a deeper understanding of the transformative initiatives spearheaded by Mr. Gadkari, as he discusses the significance of renewable energy in transportation, the integration of smart technologies, and the promotion of alternative fuels. Discover how his innovative thinking and strategic planning are paving the way for a greener, more efficient, and digitally connected India.

Beyond infrastructure, we explore Mr. Gadkari's broader vision for economic growth, job creation, and the development of rural areas. Join us for this inspiring conversation with Nitin Gadkari, a dynamic leader who is shaping the future of India's transportation landscape. Tune in to gain valuable insights and be part of the journey towards a sustainable and prosperous nation. Don't miss out - subscribe to our channel and hit the notification bell to stay updated with our latest episodes!

ùêÉùêöùê≤ ùüí:

ùêÉùêöùê≤ ùüè - ùêÖùê®ùê´ ùêâùê®ùê∞ùêöùê´ ùêëùê®ùê≠ùê¢, keep the pan on the flame & put Water & come to boil first. When the Water boiled then put Sorghum Flour/Jowar Atta to it. Mix well, cover & keep it for 5 minutes. Then knead the dough well else there will be cracks while patting roti. Finally, make chapati & enjoy with Dal, Bhindi, Curd & Sproud Salad. 

ùêÉùêöùê≤ ùüê - ùêÖùê®ùê´ ùêëùêöùê†ùê¢ ùêèùêöùê´ùêöùê≠ùê°ùêö, keep the pan on the flame & put Water & come to boil first. When the Water is boiled then put Ragi Atta & mix. Then knead the dough adding little water gradually to make firm and smooth dough. Then take a dough ball & fill the filling in it. Then flatten them with the fingers. Roast the Paratha & serve the Healthy Ragi Tawa Paratha Recipe along with Mix Dal, Dry Karele, Raita & Green Salad. 

ùêÉùêöùê≤ ùüë - ùêÖùê®ùê´ ùêëùê¢ùêúùêû ùêëùê®ùê≠ùê¢, keep the pan on the flame & put Water & come to boil first. When the Water boiled then put Rice Flour. Mix well, cover & keep it for 5 minutes. Then knead the dough well else there will be cracks while patting roti. Finally, make chapati & enjoy with Sabzi, Mango, Papad & Sproud Raita. 

ùêÉùêöùê≤ ùüí - ùêÖùê®ùê´ ùêëùê¢ùêúùêû, wash some Rice and put it in pressure cooker. Add two cups of water along with a few drops of Oil/Ghee & Salt to it. 
Turn the heat to high. Wait for 3 steams and turn off the heat & release the pressure. Serve hot & enjoy with Chhole, Salad, Curd & Dry Arbi ki sabzi. 

ùêÉùêöùê≤ ùüì - ùêÖùê®ùê´ ùêåùêÆùê•ùê≠ùê¢ùê†ùê´ùêöùê¢ùêß ùêëùê®ùê≠ùê¢, take a plate & put some Multigrain Flour & bind the dough by adding some water gradually. Cover & keep aside for some time. Then make Chapati & serve with Dal, Sabzi, Salad & Dahi Bhalla. In this way, 7 Days special thali will get ready easily.
